('b3000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000007', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222205', 'EASY', 'Strong acids are completely __ in water:', 'Dissociated', 'Associated', 'Precipitated', 'Reduced', 'A', 'Strong acids fully dissociate in water.'),
('b3000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000008', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222205', 'MEDIUM', 'For reaction A + B C + D, if Kc = 1, at equilibrium:', 'Products favored', 'Reactants favored', 'Roughly equal amounts of all', 'No reaction', 'C', 'Kc=1 means roughly equal concentrations of reactants and products.'),
('b3000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000009', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222205', 'MEDIUM', 'pH of 0.001 M HCl solution is:', '1', '2', '3', '4', 'C', 'HCl fully dissociates: [H+]=10-^3 M, pH = 3.'),
('b3000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000010', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222205', 'MEDIUM', 'Henderson-Hasselbalch equation for buffer pH is:', 'pH = pKa + log([salt]/[acid])', 'pH = pKa - log([acid]/[salt])', 'pH = pKa * [salt]', 'pH = Ka/[H+]', 'A', 'Henderson-Hasselbalch: pH = pKa + log([A-]/[HA]).'),
('b3000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000011', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222205', 'MEDIUM', 'Common ion effect suppresses:', 'Dissociation of weak electrolyte', 'Precipitation', 'Complex formation', 'Oxidation', 'A', 'Adding common ion reduces dissociation of weak electrolyte (Le Chatelier).'),
('b3000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000012', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222205', 'MEDIUM', 'Solubility product Ksp of AgCl = 1.8*10-^1^0. Solubility s is:', '1.8*10-^1^0 M', '1.34*10-^5 M', '3.6*10-^1^0 M', '1.8*10-^5 M', 'B', 'AgCl: Ksp = s^2 -> s = sqrt(1.8*10-^1^0) ~= 1.34*10-^5 M.'),
('b3000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000013', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222205', 'MEDIUM', 'Degree of dissociation of weak acid increases upon:', 'Adding strong acid', 'Dilution', 'Adding salt of weak acid', 'Increasing pressure', 'B', 'Dilution shifts equilibrium toward dissociation -> degree increases.'),
('b3000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000015', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222205', 'HARD', 'Salt of strong acid and weak base gives solution that is:', 'Acidic', 'Alkaline', 'Neutral', 'Cannot predict', 'A', 'e.g. NH Cl: NH + hydrolyzes to give acidic solution.'),
('b3000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000016', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222205', 'HARD', 'If Ka of acetic acid = 1.8*10-^5, pKa is approximately:', '4.74', '5.74', '3.74', '6.74', 'A', 'pKa = -log(1.8*10-^5) = 5 - log(1.8) ~= 4.74.'),
('b3000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000017', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222205', 'HARD', 'Kc for reverse reaction is related to Kc of forward reaction by:', 'Same value', 'Reciprocal', 'Square root', 'Double', 'B', 'K_reverse = 1/K_forward.'),
('b3000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000018', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222205', 'HARD', 'A reaction has DeltaG degrees = 0. The equilibrium constant K is:', '0', '1', 'Infinity', 'Cannot determine', 'B', 'DeltaG degrees = -RT ln K. DeltaG degrees=0 -> K=1.'),
('b3000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000019', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222205', 'HARD', 'Ostwald''s dilution law states Ka = Calpha^2 for weak acid when:', 'alpha is large', 'alpha << 1', 'alpha = 1', 'Always', 'B', 'Ka = Calpha^2/(1-alpha) ~= Calpha^2 when alpha << 1 (weak acid approximation).'),
('b3000005-0000-0000-0000-000000000020', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222205', 'HARD', 'If Q > K for a reaction, the reaction will proceed:', 'Forward', 'Backward', 'No change', 'Cannot predict', 'B', 'Q > K means too many products. reaction shifts backward to reach equilibrium.')
