('b3000008-0000-0000-0000-000000000008', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222', 'b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222208', 'MEDIUM', 'Markovnikov''s rule states that in addition of HX to alkene, H goes to carbon with:', 'More H atoms (less substituted)', 'Fewer H atoms', 'Equal H atoms', 'Halogen carbon', 'A', 'Markovnikov: H adds to carbon bearing more H atoms (more stable carbocation formed on other C).'),
